The purpose of describing its chemical purity and its manufacture were to point out in an indirect way it was produced by a central source toward some to-date unknown purpose. No megacorp or shady cabal produces something like this and sells it as a street drug just for kicks. Wondering WHY there is cosmetic variation is meant to make the reader wonder what else they don't know about its purpose. As for the slang descriptions, that was more to emphasize how many people in the world not only are aware of this SCP, but of its actual effects. Imagine an SCP well known enough to have its own slang, albeit within the more limited confines of drug culture. That was meant to suggest the difficulty of achieving the Contain in SCP, since it's reached a (comparatively) high level of exposure, presumably by design. Of course, if it is too wordy to convey that, it may well do with some condensing.







